name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
notes:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY FOR 1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all individuals aged 16 years & over. This will be at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Given the limited supply of COVID-19 vaccine available at this time and Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location you must either live or work, or get your medical care in Washington state.  Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided. 
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA SOLAMENTE PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA PRIMERA DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas de 16 años en adelante.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. 
Dado el suministro limitado de la vacuna COVID-19 disponible en este momento y el compromiso de Washington con el acceso equitativo y justo, aquellos que buscan vacunas para el COVID-19 en esta clínica deben vivir o trabajar, o recibir atención médica en el estado de Washington.  El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una. Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Lincoln Creek Lumber Clinic
notes: ****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose, Pfizer 1st/2nd dose and Moderna 2nd dose vaccine clinic. **** and is by appointment or walk in.  Please note: Johnson & Johnson and Moderna vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements. Pfizer has been authorized for ages 12 – 17 with parental authorization. This clinic is located at and hosted by the Lincoln Creek Lumber office in Chehalis in partnership with Lewis County Department of Health and Social Services, WA Department of Health and WA National Guard. This is a walk-in location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind. **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation. Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided. Please do not come if you are feeling ill.  It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. **Masks are still required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
